### Pattern C: Motion Studio / Typographic Brutalism

**When to use:** Motion studios, production companies, creative agencies whose work is visually complex (3D, VFX, motion graphics).

**Core principle:** The surrounding UI must be as quiet and stark as possible so complex portfolio pieces can breathe. Typography is massive, black, and structural.

**Motion rules:**
1. Use scroll-expanding media as the primary mechanic (see `ExpandingHero` component above)
2. The hero title splits — top half goes up, bottom half goes down — as media expands to fill the screen
3. Pacing is heavy and deliberate; easing is grounded (`power3.inOut`, not springy)
4. Section rhythm alternates between white-space-heavy typography and full-bleed media
5. Use `scrub: 1` for media expansion — smooth but substantial

**Typography style:**
```tsx
<h1 className="text-[clamp(4rem,15vw,20rem)] font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-[-0.03em] uppercase text-black">
  Studio
</h1>
```

**Layout transitions:** Stark jump from all-white typographic section to full-bleed dark media section creates impact without transitions.

